verbose_text: Despite effective systemic androgen deprivation therapy (bicalutamide, leuprolide, enzalutamide, abiraterone) with significant decrease in the testosterone level (< 10 ng/dL) and treatment with radium-223, the patient deceased after 12 months due to rapid progression of his metastatic prostate cancer with significant increase in the PSA levels from 31 ng/mL to 324 ng/mL and size of bone and lymph node metastases.
